    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. It's just hard to find the right words because the behavior feels so disruptive to the group dynamic. Like, they have this way of nipping at people or creating small, annoying friction points that just derail the energy of the room. Are there any specific professional terms or phrases that capture that kind of \"unsettling\" or \"undermining\" presence without being unprofessional?",
